\pard\sa160\fs26 \b Where DYAR stores referral information\b0\par
\pard\sa160\fs22 Referrals received via this form are stored in DYAR's case management system (Splose), DYAR's compliance and document control system (Centro Assist), and Microsoft 365 (email + OneDrive). All systems are hosted in Australia. Access is restricted by role and protected by Multi-Factor Authentication. Full details are in DYAR's Privacy Policy and in the platform-disclosure annexure to the Service Agreement signed at intake.\par
\pard\sa160\fs26 \b What happens next\b0\par
\pard\sa160\fs22 1. DYAR acknowledges receipt within 2 business days.\par
\pard\sa160\fs22 2. The Service Manager (Mehdi Dabire) reviews the referral and the participant's NDIS plan to confirm fit and funding adequacy.\par
\pard\sa160\fs22 3. We contact the participant (or nominee) within 5 business days for an intake conversation.\par
\pard\sa160\fs22 4. If we are the right provider, we send a Service Agreement + Consent Form for signature.\par
\pard\sa160\fs22 5. Service commences once both forms are signed and any pre-service risk assessment is completed.\par
\pard\sa160\fs22 If we are not the right fit, we will tell you and (where possible) suggest an alternative provider.\par
